posts.title: Unit 1, Week 1 Project: Epicode Course Introduction Page Clone
posts.body: For our first project for Epicode we were given a page used as introduction for the school and we were told to replicate as closely as possible utilizing only html and css, both of which we had been learning for only the past week.

posts.title: Unit 1, Week 2 Project: Amazon Clone
posts.body: Our second week came to an end with the assignment of cloning an amazon.com page featuring festive decorations to add, this helped us cementing the both the old and the new knowledge we had in CSS while we tried to replicate the page's design without any advanced methods.

posts.title: Unit 2, Week 1 Project: Medium Clone
posts.body: After Getting our hands dirty with JavaScript we got assigned to replicate Medium.com' Homepage, this combined all our knowledge so far into one single project, also making use of advanced CSS tools such as Flexbox

posts.title: Unit 2 Week 2 Project: Netflix Clone
posts.body: To confirm our newfound abilities at using Bootstrap we were asked to replicate Netflix.com' Home page, Settings page and Profile page using solely the framework and nothing else,

posts.title: Unit 2 Build Week Project: Spotify Clone + API
posts.body: As the finale of the second Unit, the class was divided in teams of 3 yet again to tackle the second Build Week Project where we were asked to Clone the layout and basic functionalities of Spotify.com, this included also the manipulation of data given from an external API

posts.title: Unit 3, Week 1 Project: TypeScript Introduction
posts.body: Week 4 alltogether was used mostly as a resting point for the intense lessons we had so far, but was still used to introduced us for was is yet to come, starting with Node.js and TypeScrip

posts.title: Unit 3, Build Week Project: Angular App
posts.body: After 3 weeks of TypeScript and Finally angular we had to finally say farewell to the front-end part of our journey, this time by making our own original AngularCLI application from the ground up
